                            <div type="poem">
                                <lg>
                                    <l>So rose the scene [of <placeName corresp="#SPOLETO">Spoleto</placeName>] on <persName corresp="#SR">Rogers</persName>&#x02BC; classic eye</l>
                                    <l>And thus, embalmed in words that ne&#x02BC;er could die,</l>
                                    <l>Its touching image had remained enshrined,</l>
                                    <l>Had <hi rend="italic">he</hi> to verse transferred it from his mind.</l>
                                    <l>Far other fate awaits this rustic lay,</l>
                                    <l>Framed for the passing purpose of a day:</l>
                                    <l>Enough for me if he its tone commend</l>
                                    <l>Whom &#x02BC;tis a pride and grace to call my Friend.</l>
                                </lg>
                                <lb/>
                                <p>(<ref type="bibliography" target="bibliography.php#FRIENDSHIPSOFFERING1830"><title type="annual" corresp="#FRIENDSHIPSOFFERING1830"><hi rend="italic">Friendship&#x02BC;s Offering; A Literary Album . . . for MDCCCXXX</hi></title></ref>, 111).</p>
